{"type":"user","uuid":"2e73c503-3625-47ca-b006-d058a400221f","session_id":"1a582f91-d102-4cef-bad5-528739f0d8b3","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ee7189a3e3aa4de6bc951524","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: runtime/services\n   3→PATH: src/services/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: runtime service layer for chat/session/system actions plus pipeline control facade\n   5→\n   6→KEY_FILES:\n   7→- src/services/chat-service.js\n   8→- src/services/chat-queue.js\n   9→- src/services/session-store.js\n  10→- src/services/realtime-hub.js\n  11→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n  12→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n  13→- src/services/pipeline-controller.js\n  14→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n  15→- src/services/status-aggregator.js\n  16→- src/services/log-pager.js\n  17→- src/services/telegram-pusher.js\n  18→- src/services/git-service.js\n  19→- src/services/commit-service.js\n  20→- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n  21→- src/services/output-pager-service.js\n  22→- src/services/file-service.js\n  23→- src/services/system-monitor-service.js\n  24→- src/services/alert-manager-service.js\n  25→- src/services/session-context-service.js\n  26→- src/services/alias-store.js\n  27→\n  28→PUBLIC_APIS:\n  29→- chatWithSession({ channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks })\n  30→- resetSession({ channel, sessionId })\n  31→- pipeline control: startPipeline/getPipelineStatus/stopPipeline/retryTarget/getPipelineLogs/resetTarget\n  32→- pipeline controller (F-004): createPipelineController -> startPipeline/stopPipeline/retryTarget/runSingle/getStatus/getLogs/forceUnlock\n  33→- plan ingestion: validate/save/listVersions/getVersion/setCurrent/getCurrent/rollback/getActivePath\n  34→- status aggregator (F-005): createStatusAggregator -> aggregateStatus/formatStatusForTelegram/calculateProgress/getErrorSummary\n  35→- log pager (F-005): createLogPager -> readLogPage/extractErrorLines/shouldSendAsFile/formatLogsForTelegram\n  36→- telegram pusher (F-005): createTelegramPusher -> startHeartbeat/stopHeartbeat/pushErrorSummary/sendMessageChunked/sendFile\n  37→- git service (F-008): createGitService -> getStatus/isClean/getChangedFiles/commit/amendCommit/getLastCommit/getCommitLog/getShortHash\n  38→- commit service (F-008): createCommitService -> validatePreConditions/commit/recordCommit/getSessionCommits/checkPipelineStatus/checkTestStatus/buildCommitMessage\n  39→- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n  40→- output pager (F-009): paginateOutput/storeOutputPages/getNextPage/clearPages/hasMorePages -> Telegram 4096 char limit handling\n  41→- file service (F-010): validatePath/resolveSessionPath/listDirectory/buildTree/readFile/searchFiles/writeFile/isBinaryFile -> file operations with path validation\n  42→- system monitor (F-012): getSystemInfo/getProcessList/killProcess/formatUptime/formatBytes -> CPU/memory/disk/network info, process management\n  43→- alert manager (F-012): addRule/removeRule/listRules/checkThresholds/startMonitoring/stopMonitoring/loadRules/saveRules/parseRuleString -> threshold alerting with persistence\n  44→- session context (F-013): sessionContextService -> initSessionContext/createSession/getOrCreateSession/touchSession/cleanupSession/persistSession/restoreSessions/startTimeoutWatcher/stopTimeoutWatcher/setNotificationCallback\n  45→- alias store (F-013): aliasStore -> initAliasStore/setAlias/getAlias/getAllAliases/deleteAlias/resolveAlias/loadAliases/saveAliases\n  46→\n  47→TRAPS:\n  48→- chat operations are serialized by session key; keep async queue semantics unchanged\n  49→- pipeline-control-service must delegate to script-runner instead of shell string concatenation\n  50→- pipeline-controller must use lock-manager for concurrency protection (F-004)\n  51→- runSingle must NOT acquire lock (independent execution, D5)\n  52→- file-service validatePath checks against config.telegramFileAllowedRoots (frozen at startup)\n  53→- file-service resolves symlinks and re-validates against allowed roots for security\n  54→- session-context-service is a singleton; call initSessionContext before use\n  55→- alias-store is a singleton; call initAliasStore before use\n  56→- alias names cannot contain spaces or equals sign\n  57→- session files are stored with colon replaced by underscore in filename\n  58→\n  59→DECISIONS:\n  60→- 2026-03-10 | f001-pipeline-service | expose logs/reset methods in pipeline-control-service to satisfy US3 reusable control surface\n  61→- 2026-03-12 | f003-plan-ingestion | add plan-ingestion-service for schema validation, version management, and plan registry\n  62→- 2026-03-12 | f004-pipeline-controller | new module for unified pipeline control with lock management (D4)\n  63→- 2026-03-13 | f005-status-logs | add status-aggregator, log-pager, telegram-pusher for pipeline status aggregation and log streaming\n  64→- 2026-03-15 | f008-commit-workflow | add git-service and commit-service for commit workflow with pre-commit validation, audit logging (AC-5.3)\n  65→- 2026-03-15 | f008-exception-handling | add try-catch blocks in commit() function around validatePreConditions, gitService.commit/amendCommit, recordCommit, logAuditEntry calls to prevent crashes and ensure errors logged to audit trail\n  66→- 2026-03-16 | f009-command-executor | add command-executor-service and output-pager-service for general shell command execution with blacklist, high-risk keywords, confirmation flow, session cwd, and pagination\n  67→- 2026-03-13 | f010-file-service | add file-service for directory listing, tree building, file reading/writing, and glob search with path validation\n  68→- 2026-03-13 | f012-system-monitor | add system-monitor-service and alert-manager-service for system info, process management, and threshold-based alerting with persistence\n  69→- 2026-03-12 | f013-session-context | add session-context-service and alias-store for session lifecycle management, command history, alias persistence, and timeout handling\n  70→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ee7189a3e3aa4de6bc951524","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:29:49.641Z","_requestId":"197c31d70a614d2a931d269ab7ee2117"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"d893cda8-9b76-4ccb-85b8-9b4dc1cca488","session_id":"1a582f91-d102-4cef-bad5-528739f0d8b3","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_efabc893c8a3417fa7e819c6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: bot\n   3→PATH: src/bot/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler\n  11→- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()\n  12→- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()\n  13→- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup\n  14→- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation\n  15→- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting\n  16→- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation\n  17→- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers\n  18→\n  19→SUBDIRS:\n  20→- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch\n  21→- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations\n  22→\n  23→INTERFACES:\n  24→- Telegram Commands:\n  25→  - /start - Bot startup greeting\n  26→  - /help - Dynamic help text\n  27→  - /reset - Clear chat session\n  28→  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot\n  29→  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command\n  30→  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)\n  31→  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)\n  32→  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management\n  33→  - /status [--type=feature|bugfix] - Show aggregated pipeline status (alias: /s)\n  34→  - /logs [--lines=N] [--offset=N] [--type=feature|bugfix] [--file] - View pipeline logs with pagination (alias: /l)\n  35→  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline\n  36→  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n  37→  - /commit [--message=\"...\"] [--amend] [--force] - Commit code changes with pre-commit validation (alias: /c)\n  38→  - /commits [--count=N] - View session commit history (alias: /history)\n  39→- /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)\n  40→- /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)\n  41→- /ls [path] - List directory contents (alias: /dir) (F-010)\n  42→- /tree [path] - Display directory tree structure (F-010)\n  43→- /cat <file> - View file content (F-010)\n  44→- /head [N] <file> - View first N lines of file (F-010)\n  45→- /tail [N] <file> - View last N lines of file (F-010)\n  46→- /find <pattern> - Search files by name/glob pattern (F-010)\n  47→- /upload <path> - Upload file to specified path (F-010)\n  48→- /download <file> - Download file to Telegram (F-010)\n  49→\n  50→TRAPS:\n  51→- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n  52→- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files\n  53→- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n  54→- Registry stores normalized command names\n  55→- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param\n  56→- F-005: /status uses status-aggregator for aggregated status; /logs uses log-pager for pagination\n  57→- F-008: /commit requires pre-commit validation (pipeline status + test status); --amend/--force require admin + confirmation\n  58→\n  59→DECISIONS:\n  60→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands\n  61→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l\n  62→- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands\n  63→- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management\n  64→- 2026-03-13 | F-005-status-logs | Update /status and /logs to use status-aggregator and log-pager with pagination support\n  65→- 2026-03-15 | F-008-commit-commands | Add /commit and /commits commands with pre-commit validation, session tracking, and admin confirmation for --amend/--force\n  66→- 2026-03-16 | F-009-command-executor | Add /cd and /more commands for session cwd management and paginated output viewing; add direct text mode for shell execution\n  67→- 2026-03-13 | F-010-file-manager | Add /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download commands for file system operations with security sandbox\n  68→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_efabc893c8a3417fa7e819c6","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:29:49.642Z","_requestId":"197c31d70a614d2a931d269ab7ee2117"}
