{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313053000e14de6c223794224","session_id":"1a582f91-d102-4cef-bad5-528739f0d8b3","message":{"id":"20260313053000e14de6c223794224","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_94cfa8401b594fab88812032","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Context Snapshot: F-014 Notification and Scheduled Tasks\n\n## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n\n### Feature Description\n定时任务与通知能力，让用户可以设置自动化任务调度。支持 cron 表达式定义的周期性任务和一次性延迟任务，任务执行后自动推送结果到 Telegram。\n\n定时任务：\n- `/cron add \"*/5 * * * *\" <command>` 添加周期任务\n- `/cron add --once \"2026-03-15 10:00\" <command>` 添加一次性任务\n- `/jobs` 查看所有定时任务列表\n- `/jobs pause|resume|delete <id>` 管理任务\n\n文件监听：\n- `/watch <path>` 监听文件或目录变更，有变化时推送通知（使用 fs.watch）\n- `/unwatch <path>` 取消监听\n\n持久化：任务列表和监听规则持久化到 JSON 文件，Bot 重启后自动恢复所有任务和监听。使用 node-cron 或类似轻量级库实现调度。\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n1. 用户可通过 /cron 创建周期性定时任务，指定 cron 表达式和要执行的命令\n2. 支持一次性延迟任务，指定执行时间\n3. 定时任务执行后自动推送执行结果（stdout/stderr/退出码）到 Telegram\n4. /jobs 可查看、暂停、恢复、删除定时任务\n5. 支持 /watch 监听文件或目录变更，有变化时推送通知\n6. 定时任务和监听规则持久化存储，Bot 重启后自动恢复\n\n### Dependencies\n- F-009 - General Command Executor (completed) - provides command execution with security checks\n- F-013 - Session and Context Manager (completed) - provides session management and persistence patterns\n\n---\n\n## Section 2 — Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── adapters/\n│   └── codebuddy.js\n├── bot/\n│   ├── commands/\n│   │   ├── handlers/\n│   │   │   ├── cd.js, more.js (F-009)\n│   │   │   ├── ls.js, tree.js, cat.js, head.js, tail.js, find.js (F-010)\n│   │   │   ├── upload.js, download.js (F-010)\n│   │   │   ├── sysinfo.js, ps.js, kill.js, monitor.js (F-012)\n│   │   │   ├── history.js, alias.js, sessions.js (F-013)\n│   │   │   └── pipeline.js, bugfix.js, planner.js, status.js, logs.js, stop.js, plan.js, audit.js, commit.js, commits.js\n│   │   ├── parser.js, registry.js, validator.js, formatter.js, help.js, index.js\n│   └── telegram.js\n├── http/\n│   └── server.js\n├── pipeline-infra/\n│   ├── config-loader.js, script-runner.js, state-manager.js, lock-manager.js, path-policy.js, error-codes.js, index.js, cli-entry.js\n├── routes/\n│   └── api-routes.js\n├── security/\n│   ├── guard.js, index.js, param-sanitizer.js, confirmation-manager.js, system-guard.js, permission-guard.js\n├── services/\n│   ├── chat-service.js, chat-queue.js, session-store.js\n│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js, pipeline-controller.js\n│   ├── plan-ingestion-service.js, status-aggregator.js, log-pager.js, telegram-pusher.js\n│   ├── git-service.js, commit-service.js, audit-log-service.js\n│   ├── command-executor-service.js, output-pager-service.js, system-exec-service.js\n│   ├── file-service.js, screenshot-service.js, realtime-hub.js\n│   ├── system-monitor-service.js, alert-manager-service.js\n│   ├── session-context-service.js, alias-store.js\n│   ├── ai-cli-service.js\n│   └── index.js\n├── utils/\n│   ├── logger.js, file-utils.js, heartbeat-manager.js, markdown-v2-formatter.js\n├── config.js\n└── index.js\ntests/\n├── unit/ (mirrors src structure)\n├── integration/\n├── helpers/\n└── fixtures/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n\n### root.prizm\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L0\nPROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\nPROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\nPLATFORM: codebuddy\nLANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\nPACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\nENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n```\n\n### runtime.prizm (L1)\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L1\nMODULE: runtime\nPATH: src/**\nDESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n\nKEY_FILES:\n- src/config.js\n- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n- src/services/session-context-service.js\n- src/services/alert-manager-service.js\n- src/bot/telegram.js\n- src/bot/commands/index.js\n\nINTERFACES:\n- Command Executor: executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, pagination\n- Session Context: sessionContextService -> initSessionContext/createSession/getOrCreateSession/touchSession/cleanupSession/persistSession/restoreSessions/startTimeoutWatcher/stopTimeoutWatcher\n- Alert Manager: addRule/removeRule/listRules/checkThresholds/startMonitoring/stopMonitoring/loadRules/saveRules\n\nTRAPS:\n- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow\n- F-009: long output is paginated with /more for remaining pages\n- F-012: alert rules stored in data/alert-rules.json, persisted across restarts\n- F-013: sessions keyed by telegram chat ID (sessionKey = \"telegram:<chatId>\")\n- F-013: session timeout defaults to 30 min, configurable via SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS\n- F-013: aliases stored in data/aliases.json, persisted immediately\n- F-013: session context persisted to data/sessions/ directory\n```\n\n### runtime/services.prizm (L2)\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L2\nMODULE: runtime/services\nPATH: src/services/**\n\nPUBLIC_APIS:\n- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n- session context (F-013): sessionContextService -> initSessionContext/createSession/getOrCreateSession/touchSession/cleanupSession/persistSession/restoreSessions/startTimeoutWatcher/stopTimeoutWatcher/setNotificationCallback\n- alert manager (F-012): addRule/removeRule/listRules/checkThresholds/startMonitoring/stopMonitoring/loadRules/saveRules/parseRuleString -> threshold alerting with persistence\n\nTRAPS:\n- session-context-service is a singleton; call initSessionContext before use\n- alias-store is a singleton; call initAliasStore before use\n- session files are stored with colon replaced by underscore in filename\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n\n### src/config.js (relevant config additions for F-014)\n```javascript\nimport 'dotenv/config';\nimport { z } from 'zod';\nimport { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\nimport { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n\nconst schema = z.object({\n  // ... existing config ...\n  // F-013: Session and Context Manager\n  SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(1800000), // 30 min\n  SESSION_HISTORY_MAX: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\n  SESSION_PERSISTENCE_DIR: z.string().optional().default('data/sessions'),\n  ALIAS_PERSISTENCE_PATH: z.string().optional().default('data/aliases.json')\n});\n\n// F-014: Add these new config options\n// SCHEDULED_TASKS_PATH: z.string().optional().default('data/scheduled-tasks.json'),\n// FILE_WATCHERS_PATH: z.string().optional().default('data/file-watchers.json'),\n// MAX_SCHEDULED_TASKS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\n// MAX_FILE_WATCHERS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(50)\n```\n\n### src/services/command-executor-service.js\n```javascript\n/**\n * Command Executor Service\n * F-009: General Command Executor\n *\n * Main service for executing shell commands with:\n * - Blacklist checking\n * - High-risk keyword detection\n * - Confirmation flow for dangerous commands\n * - Session working directory support\n * - Output pagination\n * - Audit logging\n */\n\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\nimport { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\nimport { executeSystemCommand } from './system-exec-service.js';\nimport { checkCommandBlacklist, detectHighRiskKeywords } from '../security/system-guard.js';\nimport { createConfirmation, confirmAction } from '../security/confirmation-manager.js';\nimport { logAuditEntry } from './audit-log-service.js';\nimport { paginateOutput, storeOutputPages, hasMorePages } from './output-pager-service.js';\nimport { getUserRole } from '../security/permission-guard.js';\n\n/**\n * Execute a command with full security checks and pagination.\n * @param {Object} options - Execution options\n * @param {string} options.command - Command to execute\n * @param {string} options.sessionId - Session identifier\n * @param {string|number} options.userId - User ID for audit and permissions\n * @param {boolean} [options.skipConfirmation=false] - Skip confirmation (for confirmed commands)\n * @param {string} [options.confirmationId] - Confirmation ID if this is a confirmed execution\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} Execution result\n */\nexport async function executeCommand(options) {\n  const { command, sessionId, userId, skipConfirmation = false, confirmationId } = options;\n\n  // Check blacklist first\n  const blacklistResult = checkCommandBlacklist(command, config.commandBlacklist);\n  if (blacklistResult.blocked) {\n    await logAuditEntry({\n      userId,\n      role: getUserRole(userId),\n      action: 'exec',\n      params: { command },\n      result: 'denied',\n      reason: `Blacklisted command: ${blacklistResult.matchedCommand}`,\n      sessionId\n    });\n    throw new Error(`命令被拒绝：${blacklistResult.reason}`);\n  }\n\n  // Detect high-risk keywords\n  const riskResult = detectHighRiskKeywords(command, config.highRiskKeywords);\n\n  // If high-risk and not confirmed, require confirmation\n  if (riskResult.isHighRisk && !skipConfirmation && !confirmationId) {\n    const params = { command, sessionId };\n    const { confirmId, message } = createConfirmation(userId, 'exec', params);\n    await logAuditEntry({\n      userId,\n      role: getUserRole(userId),\n      action: 'exec',\n      params: { command },\n      result: 'pending_confirmation',\n      reason: `High-risk keywords: ${riskResult.detectedKeywords.join(', ')}`,\n      sessionId\n    });\n    return {\n      needsConfirmation: true,\n      confirmationId: confirmId,\n      confirmationMessage: message,\n      detectedKeywords: riskResult.detectedKeywords\n    };\n  }\n\n  // If confirmation ID provided, verify it\n  if (confirmationId) {\n    const confirmResult = confirmAction(confirmationId, userId);\n    if (!confirmResult.ok) {\n      throw new Error(`确认失败：${confirmResult.error}`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Get session cwd\n  const cwd = sessionStore.getCwd(sessionId) || process.cwd();\n\n  // Execute the command\n  let result;\n  try {\n    result = await executeSystemCommand(command, { cwd });\n  } catch (error) {\n    await logAuditEntry({\n      userId,\n      role: getUserRole(userId),\n      action: 'exec',\n      params: { command, cwd },\n      result: 'failed',\n      reason: error.message,\n      sessionId\n    });\n    throw error;\n  }\n\n  // Format output\n  const output = formatOutput(result);\n  const pages = paginateOutput(output);\n  const displayOutput = pages[0];\n\n  // Store remaining pages for /more\n  if (pages.length > 1) {\n    storeOutputPages(sessionId, pages.slice(1));\n  }\n\n  // Log successful execution\n  await logAuditEntry({\n    userId,\n    role: getUserRole(userId),\n    action: 'exec',\n    params: { command, cwd },\n    result: 'success',\n    sessionId\n  });\n\n  // F-013: Record command in history\n  sessionStore.recordCommand(sessionId, command, result.exitCode);\n\n  return {\n    stdout: result.stdout,\n    stderr: result.stderr,\n    exitCode: result.exitCode,\n    timedOut: result.timedOut,\n    output: displayOutput,\n    hasMorePages: hasMorePages(sessionId),\n    needsConfirmation: false\n  };\n}\n\nfunction formatOutput(result) {\n  const parts = [];\n  if (result.timedOut) {\n    parts.push(`⚠️ 命令执行超时，已终止进程。`);\n  }\n  parts.push(`exitCode: ${result.exitCode}`);\n  if (result.stdout) {\n    parts.push(`stdout:\\n${result.stdout}`);\n  } else {\n    parts.push(`stdout: (empty)`);\n  }\n  if (result.stderr) {\n    parts.push(`stderr:\\n${result.stderr}`);\n  } else {\n    parts.push(`stderr: (empty)`);\n  }\n  return parts.join('\\n\\n');\n}\n\nexport default { executeCommand, confirmHighRiskCommand };\n```\n\n### src/services/alert-manager-service.js (persistence pattern reference)\n```javascript\n/**\n * Alert Manager Service\n * F-012: System Monitor\n *\n * Manages alert rules, threshold monitoring, and notifications.\n * Reference for persistence pattern used in F-014.\n */\n\nimport { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { mkdir, readFile, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { join } from 'node:path';\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\n\nexport class AlertManagerService {\n  constructor(options = {}) {\n    this.dataDir = options.dataDir || config.systemMonitorDataDir;\n    this.rulesFile = options.rulesFile || 'alert-rules.json';\n    this.cooldownMs = options.cooldownMs || 5 * 60 * 1000;\n    this.rules = new Map();\n    this.lastTriggered = new Map();\n    this.monitorInterval = null;\n    this.pushCallback = null;\n  }\n\n  addRule(ruleData) {\n    this._validateRule(ruleData);\n    const id = randomUUID();\n    const rule = {\n      id,\n      metric: ruleData.metric,\n      operator: ruleData.operator,\n      threshold: ruleData.threshold,\n      enabled: ruleData.enabled ?? true,\n      createdAt: Date.now()\n    };\n    this.rules.set(id, rule);\n    return { ...rule };\n  }\n\n  removeRule(ruleId) {\n    if (!this.rules.has(ruleId)) return false;\n    this.rules.delete(ruleId);\n    this.lastTriggered.delete(ruleId);\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  listRules() {\n    return Array.from(this.rules.values()).map(rule => ({ ...rule }));\n  }\n\n  async loadRules() {\n    try {\n      const filePath = join(this.dataDir, this.rulesFile);\n      const content = await readFile(filePath, 'utf-8');\n      const rules = JSON.parse(content);\n      this.rules.clear();\n      for (const rule of rules) {\n        if (rule.id && rule.metric) {\n          this.rules.set(rule.id, rule);\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      this.rules.clear();\n    }\n  }\n\n  async saveRules() {\n    try {\n      await mkdir(this.dataDir, { recursive: true });\n      const filePath = join(this.dataDir, this.rulesFile);\n      const rules = Array.from(this.rules.values());\n      await writeFile(filePath, JSON.stringify(rules, null, 2), 'utf-8');\n    } catch (error) {\n      throw new Error(`Failed to save alert rules: ${error.message}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nexport const alertManagerService = new AlertManagerService();\nexport default AlertManagerService;\n```\n\n### src/services/session-context-service.js (singleton pattern reference)\n```javascript\n/**\n * Session Context Service\n * F-013: Session and Context Manager\n *\n * Manages session lifecycle, persistence, and timeout handling.\n * Reference for singleton and persistence patterns used in F-014.\n */\n\nimport { mkdir, readFile, writeFile, unlink, readdir } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { join } from 'node:path';\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\nimport { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n\nclass SessionContextServiceClass {\n  #dataDir = null;\n  #notificationCallback = null;\n  #timeoutWatcherId = null;\n  #isInitialized = false;\n  #timeoutMs = null;\n  #checkIntervalMs = null;\n\n  reset() {\n    this.#dataDir = null;\n    this.#notificationCallback = null;\n    if (this.#timeoutWatcherId) {\n      clearInterval(this.#timeoutWatcherId);\n      this.#timeoutWatcherId = null;\n    }\n    this.#isInitialized = false;\n  }\n\n  isInitialized() {\n    return this.#isInitialized;\n  }\n\n  initSessionContext({ dataDir, timeoutMs, checkIntervalMs }) {\n    this.#dataDir = dataDir;\n    this.#timeoutMs = timeoutMs || config.sessionTimeoutMs;\n    this.#checkIntervalMs = checkIntervalMs || 60000;\n    this.#isInitialized = true;\n  }\n\n  #checkInitialized() {\n    if (!this.#isInitialized) {\n      throw new Error('SessionContextService not initialized. Call initSessionContext first.');\n    }\n  }\n\n  async #ensureDataDir() {\n    if (this.#dataDir) {\n      await mkdir(this.#dataDir, { recursive: true });\n    }\n  }\n\n  setNotificationCallback(callback) {\n    this.#notificationCallback = callback;\n  }\n\n  async persistSession(sessionKey) {\n    this.#checkInitialized();\n    await this.#ensureDataDir();\n    const info = sessionStore.getSessionInfo(sessionKey);\n    if (!info) {\n      throw new Error(`Session ${sessionKey} not found`);\n    }\n    const data = {\n      sessionKey: info.sessionKey,\n      userId: info.userId,\n      cwd: sessionStore.getCwd(sessionKey),\n      envOverrides: sessionStore.getEnvOverrides(sessionKey),\n      commandHistory: sessionStore.getCommandHistory(sessionKey),\n      createdAt: info.createdAt,\n      lastActivityAt: info.lastActivityAt\n    };\n    const filePath = this.#getSessionFilePath(sessionKey);\n    await writeFile(filePath, JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n  }\n\n  async restoreSessions() {\n    this.#checkInitialized();\n    try {\n      const files = await readdir(this.#dataDir);\n      const sessionFiles = files.filter((f) => f.endsWith('.json'));\n      for (const file of sessionFiles) {\n        try {\n          const filePath = join(this.#dataDir, file);\n          const content = await readFile(filePath, 'utf-8');\n          const data = JSON.parse(content);\n          const idleTime = Date.now() - (data.lastActivityAt || 0);\n          if (idleTime > this.#timeoutMs) {\n            await unlink(filePath);\n            continue;\n          }\n          const { sessionKey, userId, cwd, envOverrides } = data;\n          sessionStore.touchSession(sessionKey, userId);\n          if (cwd) sessionStore.setCwd(sessionKey, cwd);\n          for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(envOverrides || {})) {\n            sessionStore.setEnvOverride(sessionKey, key, value);\n          }\n        } catch (error) {\n          console.error(`Failed to restore session from ${file}:`, error.message);\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      if (error.code !== 'ENOENT') throw error;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nexport const sessionContextService = new SessionContextServiceClass();\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.js (handler pattern reference)\n```javascript\n/**\n * /monitor Command Handler\n * F-012: System Monitor\n *\n * Reference for handler pattern with subcommands.\n */\n\nimport { alertManagerService } from '../../../services/alert-manager-service.js';\nimport { escapeMarkdownV2 } from '../../../utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js';\n\nexport const monitorMeta = {\n  name: 'monitor',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '管理系统监控告警规则',\n  usage: '/monitor <set|list|remove|enable|disable> [参数]',\n  examples: [\n    '/monitor set cpu>80',\n    '/monitor list',\n    '/monitor remove <规则ID>'\n  ],\n  params: [],\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'operator',\n  helpText: '/monitor <子命令> [参数]\\n' +\n    '子命令:\\n' +\n    '  set <规则>      添加告警规则\\n' +\n    '  list           列出所有告警规则\\n' +\n    '  remove <ID>    删除规则\\n' +\n    '  enable <ID>    启用规则\\n' +\n    '  disable <ID>   禁用规则'\n};\n\nexport function parseSubcommand(args) {\n  if (!args || args.length === 0) {\n    return { subcommand: '' };\n  }\n  const subcommand = args[0].toLowerCase();\n  const arg = args.slice(1).join(' ');\n  return { subcommand, arg };\n}\n\nexport async function handleMonitor(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply, args = [] } = handlerCtx;\n  const { subcommand, arg } = parseSubcommand(args);\n\n  switch (subcommand) {\n    case 'set':\n      await handleSet(arg, reply);\n      break;\n    case 'list':\n      await handleList(reply);\n      break;\n    case 'remove':\n      await handleRemove(arg, reply);\n      break;\n    case 'enable':\n      await handleToggle(arg, true, reply);\n      break;\n    case 'disable':\n      await handleToggle(arg, false, reply);\n      break;\n    default:\n      await reply('📋 *监控告警命令用法*\\n...');\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/telegram.js (bot initialization pattern)\n```javascript\nimport { Telegraf } from 'telegraf';\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\nimport { sessionContextService } from '../services/session-context-service.js';\nimport { aliasStore } from '../services/alias-store.js';\nimport { registerCommand, routeCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n\nexport async function createTelegramBot() {\n  const bot = new Telegraf(config.telegramBotToken, {\n    handlerTimeout: 10 * 60 * 1000\n  });\n\n  // F-013: Initialize services\n  await sessionContextService.initSessionContext({ dataDir: config.sessionPersistenceDir });\n  await aliasStore.initAliasStore({ filePath: config.aliasPersistencePath });\n\n  // F-013: Restore from disk\n  await sessionContextService.restoreSessions();\n\n  // F-013: Set up notification callback\n  sessionContextService.setNotificationCallback(async (sessionKey, userId) => {\n    try {\n      const chatId = sessionKey.replace('telegram:', '');\n      await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, '⏰ 会话因长时间未活动已超时。');\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('Failed to send timeout notification:', error);\n    }\n  });\n\n  // F-013: Start timeout watcher\n  sessionContextService.startTimeoutWatcher();\n\n  // Register commands\n  registerCommand(monitorMeta, handleMonitor);\n  // ... other commands\n\n  bot.on('text', async (ctx) => {\n    const handled = await routeCommand(ctx);\n    if (handled) return;\n    // ... fallback handling\n  });\n\n  return bot;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 5 — Existing Tests\n\n### Test patterns used in the project:\n\n```javascript\n// tests/helpers/helpers.test.js pattern\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\n\n// Singleton reset pattern for testing\nservice.reset();\n\n// Mock telegram context\nconst mockCtx = {\n  reply: vi.fn(),\n  from: { id: '123456789' },\n  chat: { id: '123456789' }\n};\n\n// Test with temporary directory\nconst tempDir = await fs.mkdtemp(path.join(os.tmpdir(), 'test-'));\n```\n\n### tests/services/alert-manager-service.test.js (persistence test pattern)\n```javascript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { AlertManagerService } from '../../src/services/alert-manager-service.js';\nimport { mkdir, rm, readFile, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { join } from 'node:path';\nimport os from 'node:os';\n\ndescribe('AlertManagerService', () => {\n  let service;\n  let tempDir;\n\n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    tempDir = await mkdtemp(join(os.tmpdir(), 'alert-test-'));\n    service = new AlertManagerService({ dataDir: tempDir });\n  });\n\n  afterEach(async () => {\n    await rm(tempDir, { recursive: true, force: true });\n  });\n\n  it('should persist rules to disk', async () => {\n    service.addRule({ metric: 'cpu', operator: '>', threshold: 80, enabled: true });\n    await service.saveRules();\n\n    const content = await readFile(join(tempDir, 'alert-rules.json'), 'utf-8');\n    const rules = JSON.parse(content);\n    expect(rules).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(rules[0].metric).toBe('cpu');\n  });\n\n  it('should restore rules from disk', async () => {\n    await writeFile(join(tempDir, 'alert-rules.json'), JSON.stringify([\n      { id: 'test-id', metric: 'memory', operator: '>=', threshold: 90, enabled: true }\n    ]));\n\n    await service.loadRules();\n    const rules = service.listRules();\n    expect(rules).toHaveLength(1);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 6 — Key Design Decisions\n\n### Architecture Decisions for F-014:\n\n1. **Scheduled Tasks Service** (new file: `src/services/scheduled-task-service.js`)\n   - Use singleton pattern like `sessionContextService`\n   - Support cron expressions via `node-cron` or `croner` library\n   - Support one-time tasks with scheduled execution\n   - Store tasks in `data/scheduled-tasks.json`\n   - On task execution, use `executeCommand` from F-009\n   - Push results to Telegram via bot instance\n\n2. **File Watcher Service** (new file: `src/services/file-watcher-service.js`)\n   - Use `fs.watch` for file/directory monitoring\n   - Store watchers in `data/file-watchers.json`\n   - Support multiple watch targets per user\n   - Debounce rapid change events (500ms default)\n   - Push notifications to Telegram on change\n\n3. **Command Handlers**\n   - `/cron` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/cron.js`\n   - `/jobs` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.js`\n   - `/watch` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/watch.js`\n\n4. **Configuration**\n   - `SCHEDULED_TASKS_PATH`: Path for task persistence\n   - `FILE_WATCHERS_PATH`: Path for watcher persistence\n   - `MAX_SCHEDULED_TASKS`: Maximum tasks allowed (default 100)\n   - `MAX_FILE_WATCHERS`: Maximum watchers allowed (default 50)\n   - `TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS`: Debounce for file changes (default 500)\n\n5. **Integration Points**\n   - Initialize services in `createTelegramBot()`\n   - Restore tasks/watchers on startup\n   - Store bot instance reference for notifications\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/014-notification-and-scheduled-tasks/context-snapshot.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":69791,"output_tokens":6101,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:31:39.296Z","_requestId":"197c31d70a614d2a931d269ab7ee2117"}
