{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130531453719e21cabbc48e2","session_id":"1a582f91-d102-4cef-bad5-528739f0d8b3","message":{"id":"202603130531453719e21cabbc48e2","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_7890fabe8d27459594feac9e","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Implementation Plan: F-014 Notification and Scheduled Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\nThis feature adds scheduled task execution and file system monitoring capabilities to PrizmClaw, with Telegram notifications for task results and file changes.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Telegram Bot (telegram.js)                  │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐              │\n│  │   /cron     │  │   /jobs     │  │   /watch    │              │\n│  │   handler   │  │   handler   │  │   handler   │              │\n│  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘              │\n└─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼─────────────────────┘\n          │                │                │\n          ▼                ▼                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Service Layer                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐       │\n│  │  ScheduledTaskService   │  │  FileWatcherService     │       │\n│  │  - addCronTask()        │  │  - addWatch()           │       │\n│  │  - addOneTimeTask()     │  │  - removeWatch()        │       │\n│  │  - listTasks()          │  │  - listWatches()        │       │\n│  │  - pauseTask()          │  │  - startWatching()      │       │\n│  │  - resumeTask()         │  │  - stopWatching()       │       │\n│  │  - deleteTask()         │  │  - restoreWatches()     │       │\n│  │  - executeTask()        │  │                         │       │\n│  └───────────┬─────────────┘  └───────────┬─────────────┘       │\n│              │                            │                      │\n│              ▼                            ▼                      │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │               executeCommand (F-009)                       │  │\n│  │               NotificationCallback                         │  │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n          │\n          ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Persistence Layer                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐       │\n│  │ data/scheduled-tasks.js │  │ data/file-watchers.json │       │\n│  └─────────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────┘       │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Data Models\n\n#### ScheduledTask\n```typescript\ninterface ScheduledTask {\n  id: string;              // UUID\n  type: 'cron' | 'once';   // Task type\n  schedule: string;        // Cron expression or ISO timestamp\n  command: string;         // Command to execute\n  chatId: string;          // Telegram chat ID for notifications\n  userId: string;          // User who created the task\n  cwd?: string;            // Working directory\n  enabled: boolean;        // Active/inactive\n  createdAt: number;       // Creation timestamp\n  lastRunAt?: number;      // Last execution timestamp\n  lastResult?: TaskResult; // Last execution result\n  nextRunAt?: number;      // Next scheduled run (computed)\n}\n\ninterface TaskResult {\n  stdout: string;\n  stderr: string;\n  exitCode: number;\n  timedOut: boolean;\n  executedAt: number;\n}\n```\n\n#### FileWatcher\n```typescript\ninterface FileWatcher {\n  id: string;              // UUID\n  path: string;            // Absolute path to watch\n  chatId: string;          // Telegram chat ID for notifications\n  userId: string;          // User who created the watcher\n  recursive: boolean;      // Watch subdirectories\n  enabled: boolean;        // Active/inactive\n  createdAt: number;       // Creation timestamp\n  lastEventAt?: number;    // Last event timestamp\n  lastEventType?: string;  // Last event type (rename/change)\n}\n```\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n### New Files\n\n1. **src/services/scheduled-task-service.js**\n   - Singleton service for managing scheduled tasks\n   - Uses `croner` library for cron parsing and scheduling\n   - Integrates with `executeCommand` from F-009\n   - Sends Telegram notifications on task completion\n\n2. **src/services/file-watcher-service.js**\n   - Singleton service for file system monitoring\n   - Uses `fs.watch` with debouncing\n   - Sends Telegram notifications on file changes\n\n3. **src/bot/commands/handlers/cron.js**\n   - Handler for `/cron add` command\n   - Validates cron expressions and timestamps\n   - Delegates to ScheduledTaskService\n\n4. **src/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.js**\n   - Handler for `/jobs` command with subcommands\n   - list/pause/resume/delete operations\n\n5. **src/bot/commands/handlers/watch.js**\n   - Handler for `/watch` and `/unwatch` commands\n   - Delegates to FileWatcherService\n\n### Modified Files\n\n1. **src/config.js**\n   - Add F-014 configuration options\n\n2. **src/bot/telegram.js**\n   - Initialize services on startup\n   - Restore tasks and watchers from disk\n   - Register new command handlers\n\n3. **src/services/index.js**\n   - Export new services\n\n## Testing Approach\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **tests/services/scheduled-task-service.test.js**\n   - Test cron expression parsing\n   - Test one-time task scheduling\n   - Test task CRUD operations\n   - Test persistence save/load\n\n2. **tests/services/file-watcher-service.test.js**\n   - Test watcher CRUD operations\n   - Test persistence save/load\n   - Test debouncing logic\n\n3. **tests/bot/commands/handlers/cron.test.js**\n   - Test command parsing\n   - Test validation errors\n   - Test success flows\n\n4. **tests/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.test.js**\n   - Test subcommand routing\n   - Test list formatting\n   - Test pause/resume/delete\n\n5. **tests/bot/commands/handlers/watch.test.js**\n   - Test watch/unwatch commands\n   - Test path validation\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **tests/integration/f014-scheduled-tasks.test.js**\n   - End-to-end task lifecycle\n   - Bot notification on execution\n   - Persistence across restart\n\n2. **tests/integration/f014-file-watchers.test.js**\n   - File change detection\n   - Bot notification on change\n   - Persistence across restart\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n1. Config changes (src/config.js)\n2. ScheduledTaskService (core functionality)\n3. FileWatcherService (core functionality)\n4. Command handlers (cron, jobs, watch)\n5. Bot integration (telegram.js)\n6. Unit tests\n7. Integration tests\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### npm packages to add\n- `croner` - Lightweight cron parser and scheduler (alternative: `node-cron`)\n\n```bash\nnpm install croner\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Task Execution**: Uses existing `executeCommand` with blacklist and high-risk checks\n2. **Path Validation**: File watchers restricted to `TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS`\n3. **Rate Limiting**: Maximum tasks/watchers per user (configurable)\n4. **Audit Logging**: All task/watcher changes logged\n\n## Telegram Notification Format\n\n### Task Execution Result\n```\n⏰ 定时任务完成\n\n任务ID: abc123\n命令: echo \"hello\"\n执行时间: 2026-03-13 10:00:00\n\nexitCode: 0\nstdout:\nhello\n\nstderr: (empty)\n```\n\n### File Change Notification\n```\n📁 文件变更检测\n\n路径: /path/to/file.txt\n事件: 修改\n时间: 2026-03-13 10:00:00\n```\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/014-notification-and-scheduled-tasks/plan.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":75938,"output_tokens":1886,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_inp