ndleCron\n  37→- [x] Implement /cron add <cron-expr> <command> parsing\n  38→- [x] Implement /cron add --once <datetime> <command> parsing\n  39→- [x] Add validation for cron expressions and datetime formats\n  40→- [x] Create src/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.js with jobsMeta and handleJobs\n  41→- [x] Implement /jobs list subcommand\n  42→- [x] Implement /jobs pause <id> subcommand\n  43→- [x] Implement /jobs resume <id> subcommand\n  44→- [x] Implement /jobs delete <id> subcommand\n  45→- [x] Create src/bot/commands/handlers/watch.js with watchMeta and handleWatch\n  46→- [x] Implement /watch <path> command\n  47→- [x] Implement /unwatch <path> command\n  48→\n  49→## Phase 5: Bot Integration\n  50→\n  51→- [x] Import new services in src/bot/telegram.js\n  52→- [x] Import new command handlers in src/bot/telegram.js\n  53→- [x] Initialize scheduledTaskService in createTelegramBot()\n  54→- [x] Initialize fileWatcherService in createTelegramBot()\n  55→- [x] Set up notification callbacks with bot.telegram reference\n  56→- [x] Restore tasks and watchers from disk on startup\n  57→- [x] Register /cron, /jobs, /watch commands\n  58→- [x] Add services to src/services/index.js exports\n  59→\n  60→## Phase 6: Unit Tests\n  61→\n  62→- [x] Create tests/config/f014-config.test.js for config validation\n  63→- [x] Create tests/services/scheduled-task-service.test.js\n  64→- [x] Test cron task creation and scheduling\n  65→- [x] Test one-time task creation\n  66→- [x] Test task CRUD operations\n  67→- [x] Test persistence save/load\n  68→- [x] Create tests/services/file-watcher-service.test.js\n  69→- [x] Test watcher CRUD operations\n  70→- [x] Test path validation\n  71→- [x] Test persistence save/load\n  72→- [x] Create tests/bot/commands/handlers/cron.test.js\n  73→- [x] Create tests/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.test.js\n  74→- [x] Create tests/bot/commands/handlers/watch.test.js\n  75→\n  76→## Phase 7: Integration Tests\n  77→\n  78→- [ ] Create tests/integration/f014-sch