{"type":"user","uuid":"fa3ee0f5-0002-4a1d-b506-190f206d790f","session_id":"1a582f91-d102-4cef-bad5-528739f0d8b3","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce404738de20723b81650b28ef6f1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: bot\n   3→PATH: src/bot/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler\n  11→- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()\n  12→- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()\n  13→- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup\n  14→- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation\n  15→- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting\n  16→- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation\n  17→- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers\n  18→\n  19→SUBDIRS:\n  20→- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch\n  21→- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations\n  22→\n  23→INTERFACES:\n  24→- Telegram Commands:\n  25→  - /start - Bot startup greeting\n  26→  - /help - Dynamic help text\n  27→  - /reset - Clear chat session\n  28→  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot\n  29→  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command\n  30→  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)\n  31→  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)\n  32→  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management\n  33→  - /status [--type=feature|bugfix] - Show aggregated pipeline status (alias: /s)\n  34→  - /logs [--lines=N] [--offset=N] [--type=feature|bugfix] [--file] - View pipeline logs with pagination (alias: /l)\n  35→  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline\n  36→  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n  37→  - /commit [--message=\"...\"] [--amend] [--force] - Commit code changes with pre-commit validation (alias: /c)\n  38→  - /commits [--count=N] - View session commit history (alias: /history)\n  39→- /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)\n  40→- /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)\n  41→- /ls [path] - List directory contents (alias: /dir) (F-010)\n  42→- /tree [path] - Display directory tree structure (F-010)\n  43→- /cat <file> - View file content (F-010)\n  44→- /head [N] <file> - View first N lines of file (F-010)\n  45→- /tail [N] <file> - View last N lines of file (F-010)\n  46→- /find <pattern> - Search files by name/glob pattern (F-010)\n  47→- /upload <path> - Upload file to specified path (F-010)\n  48→- /download <file> - Download file to Telegram (F-010)\n  49→\n  50→TRAPS:\n  51→- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n  52→- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files\n  53→- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n  54→- Registry stores normalized command names\n  55→- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param\n  56→- F-005: /status uses status-aggregator for aggregated status; /logs uses log-pager for pagination\n  57→- F-008: /commit requires pre-commit validation (pipeline status + test status); --amend/--force require admin + confirmation\n  58→\n  59→DECISIONS:\n  60→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands\n  61→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l\n  62→- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands\n  63→- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management\n  64→- 2026-03-13 | F-005-status-logs | Update /status and /logs to use status-aggregator and log-pager with pagination support\n  65→- 2026-03-15 | F-008-commit-commands | Add /commit and /commits commands with pre-commit validation, session tracking, and admin confirmation for --amend/--force\n  66→- 2026-03-16 | F-009-command-executor | Add /cd and /more commands for session cwd management and paginated output viewing; add direct text mode for shell execution\n  67→- 2026-03-13 | F-010-file-manager | Add /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download commands for file system operations with security sandbox\n  68→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_a081f83b25834f26a2e6a43e","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:47:03.464Z","_requestId":"0897e02cbc65495fa1b66af82a5de7ab"}
