{"type":"user","uuid":"bb5e1307-d8f6-4be8-b570-d4ef6b9251d2","session_id":"1a582f91-d102-4cef-bad5-528739f0d8b3","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce40505cbc2ee5cda87bc7f30a1fc","content":[{"type":"text","text":" 720→## Section 6 — Key Design Decisions\n 721→\n 722→### Architecture Decisions for F-014:\n 723→\n 724→1. **Scheduled Tasks Service** (new file: `src/services/scheduled-task-service.js`)\n 725→   - Use singleton pattern like `sessionContextService`\n 726→   - Support cron expressions via `node-cron` or `croner` library\n 727→   - Support one-time tasks with scheduled execution\n 728→   - Store tasks in `data/scheduled-tasks.json`\n 729→   - On task execution, use `executeCommand` from F-009\n 730→   - Push results to Telegram via bot instance\n 731→\n 732→2. **File Watcher Service** (new file: `src/services/file-watcher-service.js`)\n 733→   - Use `fs.watch` for file/directory monitoring\n 734→   - Store watchers in `data/file-watchers.json`\n 735→   - Support multiple watch targets per user\n 736→   - Debounce rapid change events (500ms default)\n 737→   - Push notifications to Telegram on change\n 738→\n 739→3. **Command Handlers**\n 740→   - `/cron` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/cron.js`\n 741→   - `/jobs` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.js`\n 742→   - `/watch` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/watch.js`\n 743→\n 744→4. **Configuration**\n 745→   - `SCHEDULED_TASKS_PATH`: Path for task persistence\n 746→   - `FILE_WATCHERS_PATH`: Path for watcher persistence\n 747→   - `MAX_SCHEDULED_TASKS`: Maximum tasks allowed (default 100)\n 748→   - `MAX_FILE_WATCHERS`: Maximum watchers allowed (default 50)\n 749→   - `TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS`: Debounce for file changes (default 500)\n 750→\n 751→5. **Integration Points**\n 752→   - Initialize services in `createTelegramBot()`\n 753→   - Restore tasks/watchers on startup\n 754→   - Store bot instance reference for notifications\n 755→\n 756→---\n 757→\n 758→## Implementation Log\n 759→\n 760→### Files Created\n 761→\n 762→1. **src/services/scheduled-task-service.js**\n 763→   - Singleton service for managing scheduled tasks\n 764→   - Supports cron expressions and one-time tasks via `croner` library\n 765→   - Implements addCronTask, addOneTimeTask, listTasks, pauseTask, resumeTask, deleteTask, executeTask\n 766→   - Includes persistence (saveTasks/loadTasks), scheduler lifecycle (startScheduler/stopScheduler)\n 767→   - Integrates with executeCommand for task execution and Telegram for notifications\n 768→\n 769→2. **src/services/file-watcher-service.js**\n 770→   - Singleton service for file system monitoring\n 771→   - Uses native `fs.watch` with configurable debouncing (default 500ms)\n 772→   - Implements addWatch, removeWatch, listWatches, startWatching, stopWatching, stopAllWatchers\n 773→   - Includes persistence (saveWatches/loadWatches), restoreWatches for restart recovery\n 774→   - Path validation against allowed roots (TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS)\n 775→\n 776→3. **src/bot/commands/handlers/cron.js**\n 777→   - Handler for /cron add command\n 778→   - Parses cron expressions and datetime strings for one-time tasks\n 779→   - Validates cron expressions using croner library\n 780→   - Delegates to scheduledTaskService\n 781→\n 782→4. **src/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.js**\n 783→   - Handler for /jobs command with subcommands: list, pause, resume, delete\n 784→   - Supports partial ID matching for task operations\n 785→   - Filters tasks by chatId\n 786→\n 787→5. **src/bot/commands/handlers/watch.js**\n 788→   - Handler for /watch and /unwatch commands\n 789→   - Supports /watch list, /watch <path>, /unwatch <path|ID>\n 790→   - Path validation and normalization\n 791→\n 792→### Files Modified\n 793→\n 794→1. **src/config.js**\n 795→   - Added F-014 config options:\n 796→     - SCHEDULED_TASKS_PATH (default: 'data/scheduled-tasks.json')\n 797→     - FILE_WATCHERS_PATH (default: 'data/file-watchers.json')\n 798→     - MAX_SCHEDULED_TASKS (default: 100)\n 799→     - MAX_FILE_WATCHERS (default: 50)\n 800→     - TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS (default: 500)\n 801→\n 802→2. **src/services/index.js**\n 803→   - Exported scheduledTaskService and fileWatcherService\n 804→\n 805→3. **src/bot/telegram.js**\n 806→   - Imported F-014 services and command handlers\n 807→   - Initialized scheduledTaskService with executeCallback and notificationCallback\n 808→   - Initialized fileWatcherService with notificationCallback\n 809→   - Added service restoration on startup (loadTasks, loadWatches, restoreWatches)\n 810→   - Registered /cron, /jobs, /watch commands\n 811→   - Added helper function truncate() for output formatting\n 812→\n 813→4. **package.json**\n 814→   - Added dependency: croner (^9.0.0)\n 815→\n 816→### Key Implementation Decisions\n 817→\n 818→1. **Cron Library Selection**\n 819→   - Chose `croner` over `node-cron` for its lightweight footprint and clean API\n 820→   - Supports standard 5-field cron expressions\n 821→   - Provides nextRun calculation for task scheduling\n 822→\n 823→2. **Singleton Pattern**\n 824→   - Both services use singleton pattern similar to sessionContextService\n 825→   - Reset method for testing isolation\n 826→   - Init methods for configuration injection\n 827→\n 828→3. **Task Execution Flow**\n 829→   - Tasks use executeCommand with skipConfirmation=true (scheduled tasks are pre-approved)\n 830→   - Results captured in lastResult field with stdout/stderr/exitCode/timedOut\n 831→   - Telegram notifications sent via callback pattern for decoupling\n 832→\n 833→4. **File Watcher Debouncing**\n 834→   - 500ms default debounce to prevent rapid-fire notifications\n 835→   - Configurable via TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n 836→   - Per-watcher debounce timers for independent operation\n 837→\n 838→5. **Persistence Strategy**\n 839→   - Tasks/watchers stored as JSON arrays in data/ directory\n 840→   - Loaded on startup with graceful handling of missing/corrupted files\n 841→   - One-time tasks automatically deleted after execution\n 842→\n 843→### Deviations from plan.md\n 844→\n 845→1. **No separate bot.prizm update needed**\n 846→   - runtime.prizm and services.prizm already contained sufficient documentation\n 847→   - Command documentation added to INTERFACES section of runtime.prizm\n 848→\n 849→2. **Added setExecuteCallback method**\n 850→   - Not in original plan but necessary for clean integration with executeCommand\n 851→   - Allows service to delegate command execution to the configured callback\n 852→\n 853→3. **Added truncate helper to telegram.js**\n 854→   - Utility function for truncating long output in notifications\n 855→   - Keeps Telegram messages within reasonable limits\n 856→\n 857→### Test Coverage\n 858→\n 859→- 87 tests total across unit and integration tests\n 860→- Config validation: 6 tests\n 861→- ScheduledTaskService: 25 tests\n 862→- FileWatcherService: 21 tests\n 863→- Command handlers (cron, jobs, watch): 21 tests\n 864→- Integration tests: 14 tests\n 865→\n 866→All tests pass successfully.\n 867→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_a081f83b25834f26a2e6a43e","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:47:41.167Z","_requestId":"0897e02cbc65495fa1b66af82a5de7ab"}
