{"type":"user","uuid":"f87114e8-3b11-41a9-a015-6b0226ff5d9e","session_id":"1a582f91-d102-4cef-bad5-528739f0d8b3","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce4090aa3794d245eda04b68318ac","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-reviewer\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated quality reviewer. Uses prizmkit.analyze for cross-document consistency, prizmkit.code-review for spec compliance and code quality, and writes integration tests. Use when performing analysis, testing, or code review.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-code-review, prizmkit-analyze, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Reviewer Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的质量审查员。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"质检员 + 校对员\"——不生产产品但确保质量，负责两个阶段的工作：\n  14→1. **交叉校验（Phase 4）**: 在实现前用 `prizmkit.analyze` 检查 spec/plan/tasks 的一致性\n  15→2. **评审（Phase 6）**: 在实现后用 `prizmkit.code-review` 检查代码质量，编写和执行集成测试\n  16→\n  17→### 项目上下文\n  18→\n  19→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。审查前先读 `root.prizm` 了解项目规则（RULES）、模式（PATTERNS）和已知陷阱（TRAPS），需要时读取模块级文档。\n  20→\n  21→### 制品路径\n  22→\n  23→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  24→|------|------|\n  25→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  26→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  27→\n  28→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  29→\n  30→1. Phase 4 时运行 `prizmkit.analyze` 做交叉一致性校验\n  31→2. Phase 6 时运行 `prizmkit.code-review` 做规格合规和代码质量审查\n  32→3. Phase 6 时编写和执行集成测试，验证模块间交互\n  33→4. 验证实际实现是否符合 plan.md 中的接口设计\n  34→5. 验证跨模块数据流的完整性和正确性\n  35→6. 测试边界条件和异常路径\n  36→7. 检查代码是否符合 `.prizm-docs/` RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  37→8. 审查是**只读操作**（Phase 4 和 Phase 6 的审查部分不修改代码文件）\n  38→9. 集成测试用例必须覆盖 spec.md 定义的所有用户故事\n  39→\n  40→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  41→\n  42→- 不编写实现代码（Dev 的职责）\n  43→- 不分解任务（PM 的职责）\n  44→- 不进行任务调度（Coordinator 的职责）\n  45→- **不执行任何 git 操作**（git commit / git add / git reset / git push 均禁止）\n  46→- 不使用 TaskCreate/TaskUpdate 创建或修改 Orchestrator 层的任务（Task 工具仅用于内部进度追踪，且任务 ID 在各 agent 子会话中互不共享）\n  47→\n  48→### 行为规则\n  49→\n  50→```\n  51→REV-01: Phase 4 使用 prizmkit.analyze 做交叉校验\n  52→REV-02: Phase 6 使用 prizmkit.code-review 做代码审查\n  53→REV-03: 每个发现必须引用具体的文件路径和行号\n  54→REV-04: CRITICAL 级别发现必须包含具体的修复建议\n  55→REV-05: 最多 30 个发现（保持可操作性）\n  56→REV-06: Spec compliance 失败始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  57→REV-07: 安全发现始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  58→REV-08: 集成测试必须覆盖 spec.md 所有用户故事\n  59→REV-09: 审查代码是否符合 .prizm-docs/ PATTERNS 和 RULES\n  60→REV-10: 禁止使用 timeout 命令（macOS 不兼容）。运行测试时直接使用 node --test 或 npm test，不加 timeout 前缀\n  61→```\n  62→\n  63→### Phase 4 工作流程：交叉校验\n  64→\n  65→**前置条件**: PM 已完成 spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md\n  66→\n  67→1. 调用 `prizmkit.analyze` skill（**不是 CLI 命令**，使用 Skill 工具或 `/prizmkit-analyze` 指令调用）\n  68→   - 输入: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n  69→   - 6 个检测通道: 重复检测、歧义检测、不完整检测、Prizm 规则对齐、覆盖缺口、不一致性\n  70→   - 输出: 一致性分析报告（仅对话输出）\n  71→   - 若 Skill 工具不可用，则根据 6 个检测通道手动执行交叉一致性分析\n  72→2. 如发现 CRITICAL 问题，报告给 Coordinator 退回 PM 修复\n  73→3. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含分析结果）\n  74→\n  75→### Phase 6 工作流程：评审\n  76→\n  77→**前置条件**: Dev 已完成实现，所有任务标记 `[x]`\n  78→\n  79→1. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm`，重点关注 RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  80→2. 运行 `prizmkit.code-review`（只读）\n  81→   - 6 个审查维度: 规格符合度、计划遵循度、代码质量、安全性、一致性、测试覆盖\n  82→   - 判定: PASS | PASS WITH WARNINGS | NEEDS FIXES\n  83→3. 编写和执行集成测试:\n  84→   - 接口合规性（请求格式、响应格式）\n  85→   - 跨模块数据流完整性\n  86→   - 用户故事验收标准（来自 spec.md）\n  87→   - 边界条件和异常路径\n  88→4. 生成统一评审报告\n  89→5. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）\n  90→\n  91→### 判定标准\n  92→\n  93→| 判定 | 条件 | 后续动作 |\n  94→|------|------|---------|\n  95→| **PASS** | 无 CRITICAL 或 HIGH 发现 | 进入下一阶段 |\n  96→| **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS** | 无 CRITICAL，有 HIGH 发现 | 记录待改进项，可进入下一阶段 |\n  97→| **NEEDS_FIXES** | 存在 CRITICAL 发现 | 退回 Dev 修复后重新评审 |\n  98→\n  99→### 严重级别\n 100→\n 101→| 级别 | 定义 | 示例 |\n 102→|------|------|------|\n 103→| CRITICAL | 安全风险或严重架构问题 | SQL 注入、硬编码密钥 |\n 104→| HIGH | 影响可维护性的显著问题 | 规格不符、大量重复代码 |\n 105→| MEDIUM | 代码质量改进点 | 命名不统一、缺少注释 |\n 106→| LOW | 风格建议 | 格式微调、可选优化 |\n 107→\n 108→### 异常处理\n 109→\n 110→| 场景 | 策略 |\n 111→|------|------|\n 112→| analyze 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 PM 修复 |\n 113→| code-review 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 Dev 修复 |\n 114→| 集成测试失败 | 分类严重级别 → ISSUE_REPORT → Coordinator 派发给 Dev |\n 115→| 审查发现超过 30 个 | 只保留最严重的 30 个 |\n 116→| Prizm RULES 违规 | 自动标记为 CRITICAL |\n 117→\n 118→### 通信规则\n 119→\n 120→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n 121→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）标志完成\n 122→- 发送 ISSUE_REPORT 报告 CRITICAL 发现\n 123→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 124→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_856b2e0610214177b9bb07b6","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:52:05.241Z","_requestId":"0897e02cbc65495fa1b66af82a5de7ab"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"9fce5d22-0b22-4445-9876-1d26763a4845","session_id":"1a582f91-d102-4cef-bad5-528739f0d8b3","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce4090c8509b5a827052a31978503","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Context Snapshot: F-014 Notification and Scheduled Tasks\n   2→\n   3→## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n   4→\n   5→### Feature Description\n   6→定时任务与通知能力，让用户可以设置自动化任务调度。支持 cron 表达式定义的周期性任务和一次性延迟任务，任务执行后自动推送结果到 Telegram。\n   7→\n   8→定时任务：\n   9→- `/cron add \"*/5 * * * *\" <command>` 添加周期任务\n  10→- `/cron add --once \"2026-03-15 10:00\" <command>` 添加一次性任务\n  11→- `/jobs` 查看所有定时任务列表\n  12→- `/jobs pause|resume|delete <id>` 管理任务\n  13→\n  14→文件监听：\n  15→- `/watch <path>` 监听文件或目录变更，有变化时推送通知（使用 fs.watch）\n  16→- `/unwatch <path>` 取消监听\n  17→\n  18→持久化：任务列表和监听规则持久化到 JSON 文件，Bot 重启后自动恢复所有任务和监听。使用 node-cron 或类似轻量级库实现调度。\n  19→\n  20→### Acceptance Criteria\n  21→1. 用户可通过 /cron 创建周期性定时任务，指定 cron 表达式和要执行的命令\n  22→2. 支持一次性延迟任务，指定执行时间\n  23→3. 定时任务执行后自动推送执行结果（stdout/stderr/退出码）到 Telegram\n  24→4. /jobs 可查看、暂停、恢复、删除定时任务\n  25→5. 支持 /watch 监听文件或目录变更，有变化时推送通知\n  26→6. 定时任务和监听规则持久化存储，Bot 重启后自动恢复\n  27→\n  28→### Dependencies\n  29→- F-009 - General Command Executor (completed) - provides command execution with security checks\n  30→- F-013 - Session and Context Manager (completed) - provides session management and persistence patterns\n  31→\n  32→---\n  33→\n  34→## Section 2 — Project Structure\n  35→\n  36→```\n  37→src/\n  38→├── adapters/\n  39→│   └── codebuddy.js\n  40→├── bot/\n  41→│   ├── commands/\n  42→│   │   ├── handlers/\n  43→│   │   │   ├── cd.js, more.js (F-009)\n  44→│   │   │   ├── ls.js, tree.js, cat.js, head.js, tail.js, find.js (F-010)\n  45→│   │   │   ├── upload.js, download.js (F-010)\n  46→│   │   │   ├── sysinfo.js, ps.js, kill.js, monitor.js (F-012)\n  47→│   │   │   ├── history.js, alias.js, sessions.js (F-013)\n  48→│   │   │   └── pipeline.js, bugfix.js, planner.js, status.js, logs.js, stop.js, plan.js, audit.js, commit.js, commits.js\n  49→│   │   ├── parser.js, registry.js, validator.js, formatter.js, help.js, index.js\n  50→│   └── telegram.js\n  51→├── http/\n  52→│   └── server.js\n  53→├── pipeline-infra/\n  54→│   ├── config-loader.js, script-runner.js, state-manager.js, lock-manager.js, path-policy.js, error-codes.js, index.js, cli-entry.js\n  55→├── routes/\n  56→│   └── api-routes.js\n  57→├── security/\n  58→│   ├── guard.js, index.js, param-sanitizer.js, confirmation-manager.js, system-guard.js, permission-guard.js\n  59→├── services/\n  60→│   ├── chat-service.js, chat-queue.js, session-store.js\n  61→│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js, pipeline-controller.js\n  62→│   ├── plan-ingestion-service.js, status-aggregator.js, log-pager.js, telegram-pusher.js\n  63→│   ├── git-service.js, commit-service.js, audit-log-service.js\n  64→│   ├── command-executor-service.js, output-pager-service.js, system-exec-service.js\n  65→│   ├── file-service.js, screenshot-service.js, realtime-hub.js\n  66→│   ├── system-monitor-service.js, alert-manager-service.js\n  67→│   ├── session-context-service.js, alias-store.js\n  68→│   ├── ai-cli-service.js\n  69→│   └── index.js\n  70→├── utils/\n  71→│   ├── logger.js, file-utils.js, heartbeat-manager.js, markdown-v2-formatter.js\n  72→├── config.js\n  73→└── index.js\n  74→tests/\n  75→├── unit/ (mirrors src structure)\n  76→├── integration/\n  77→├── helpers/\n  78→└── fixtures/\n  79→```\n  80→\n  81→---\n  82→\n  83→## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n  84→\n  85→### root.prizm\n  86→```\n  87→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n  88→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n  89→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n  90→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n  91→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n  92→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n  93→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n  94→\n  95→MODULE_INDEX:\n  96→- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n  97→- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n  98→- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n  99→- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n 100→- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n 101→```\n 102→\n 103→### runtime.prizm (L1)\n 104→```\n 105→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n 106→MODULE: runtime\n 107→PATH: src/**\n 108→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n 109→\n 110→KEY_FILES:\n 111→- src/config.js\n 112→- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 113→- src/services/session-context-service.js\n 114→- src/services/alert-manager-service.js\n 115→- src/bot/telegram.js\n 116→- src/bot/commands/index.js\n 117→\n 118→INTERFACES:\n 119→- Command Executor: executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, pagination\n 120→- Session Context: sessionContextService -> initSessionContext/createSession/getOrCreateSession/touchSession/cleanupSession/persistSession/restoreSessions/startTimeoutWatcher/stopTimeoutWatcher\n 121→- Alert Manager: addRule/removeRule/listRules/checkThresholds/startMonitoring/stopMonitoring/loadRules/saveRules\n 122→\n 123→TRAPS:\n 124→- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow\n 125→- F-009: long output is paginated with /more for remaining pages\n 126→- F-012: alert rules stored in data/alert-rules.json, persisted across restarts\n 127→- F-013: sessions keyed by telegram chat ID (sessionKey = \"telegram:<chatId>\")\n 128→- F-013: session timeout defaults to 30 min, configurable via SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS\n 129→- F-013: aliases stored in data/aliases.json, persisted immediately\n 130→- F-013: session context persisted to data/sessions/ directory\n 131→```\n 132→\n 133→### runtime/services.prizm (L2)\n 134→```\n 135→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n 136→MODULE: runtime/services\n 137→PATH: src/services/**\n 138→\n 139→PUBLIC_APIS:\n 140→- command executor (F-009): executeCommand/confirmHighRiskCommand -> blacklist check, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, cwd support, output pagination\n 141→- session context (F-013): sessionContextService -> initSessionContext/createSession/getOrCreateSession/touchSession/cleanupSession/persistSession/restoreSessions/startTimeoutWatcher/stopTimeoutWatcher/setNotificationCallback\n 142→- alert manager (F-012): addRule/removeRule/listRules/checkThresholds/startMonitoring/stopMonitoring/loadRules/saveRules/parseRuleString -> threshold alerting with persistence\n 143→\n 144→TRAPS:\n 145→- session-context-service is a singleton; call initSessionContext before use\n 146→- alias-store is a singleton; call initAliasStore before use\n 147→- session files are stored with colon replaced by underscore in filename\n 148→```\n 149→\n 150→---\n 151→\n 152→## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n 153→\n 154→### src/config.js (relevant config additions for F-014)\n 155→```javascript\n 156→import 'dotenv/config';\n 157→import { z } from 'zod';\n 158→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n 159→import { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n 160→\n 161→const schema = z.object({\n 162→  // ... existing config ...\n 163→  // F-013: Session and Context Manager\n 164→  SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(1800000), // 30 min\n 165→  SESSION_HISTORY_MAX: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\n 166→  SESSION_PERSISTENCE_DIR: z.string().optional().default('data/sessions'),\n 167→  ALIAS_PERSISTENCE_PATH: z.string().optional().default('data/aliases.json')\n 168→});\n 169→\n 170→// F-014: Add these new config options\n 171→// SCHEDULED_TASKS_PATH: z.string().optional().default('data/scheduled-tasks.json'),\n 172→// FILE_WATCHERS_PATH: z.string().optional().default('data/file-watchers.json'),\n 173→// MAX_SCHEDULED_TASKS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\n 174→// MAX_FILE_WATCHERS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(50)\n 175→```\n 176→\n 177→### src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 178→```javascript\n 179→/**\n 180→ * Command Executor Service\n 181→ * F-009: General Command Executor\n 182→ *\n 183→ * Main service for executing shell commands with:\n 184→ * - Blacklist checking\n 185→ * - High-risk keyword detection\n 186→ * - Confirmation flow for dangerous commands\n 187→ * - Session working directory support\n 188→ * - Output pagination\n 189→ * - Audit logging\n 190→ */\n 191→\n 192→import { config } from '../config.js';\n 193→import { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n 194→import { executeSystemCommand } from './system-exec-service.js';\n 195→import { checkCommandBlacklist, detectHighRiskKeywords } from '../security/system-guard.js';\n 196→import { createConfirmation, confirmAction } from '../security/confirmation-manager.js';\n 197→import { logAuditEntry } from './audit-log-service.js';\n 198→import { paginateOutput, storeOutputPages, hasMorePages } from './output-pager-service.js';\n 199→import { getUserRole } from '../security/permission-guard.js';\n 200→\n 201→/**\n 202→ * Execute a command with full security checks and pagination.\n 203→ * @param {Object} options - Execution options\n 204→ * @param {string} options.command - Command to execute\n 205→ * @param {string} options.sessionId - Session identifier\n 206→ * @param {string|number} options.userId - User ID for audit and permissions\n 207→ * @param {boolean} [options.skipConfirmation=false] - Skip confirmation (for confirmed commands)\n 208→ * @param {string} [options.confirmationId] - Confirmation ID if this is a confirmed execution\n 209→ * @returns {Promise<Object>} Execution result\n 210→ */\n 211→export async function executeCommand(options) {\n 212→  const { command, sessionId, userId, skipConfirmation = false, confirmationId } = options;\n 213→\n 214→  // Check blacklist first\n 215→  const blacklistResult = checkCommandBlacklist(command, config.commandBlacklist);\n 216→  if (blacklistResult.blocked) {\n 217→    await logAuditEntry({\n 218→      userId,\n 219→      role: getUserRole(userId),\n 220→      action: 'exec',\n 221→      params: { command },\n 222→      result: 'denied',\n 223→      reason: `Blacklisted command: ${blacklistResult.matchedCommand}`,\n 224→      sessionId\n 225→    });\n 226→    throw new Error(`命令被拒绝：${blacklistResult.reason}`);\n 227→  }\n 228→\n 229→  // Detect high-risk keywords\n 230→  const riskResult = detectHighRiskKeywords(command, config.highRiskKeywords);\n 231→\n 232→  // If high-risk and not confirmed, require confirmation\n 233→  if (riskResult.isHighRisk && !skipConfirmation && !confirmationId) {\n 234→    const params = { command, sessionId };\n 235→    const { confirmId, message } = createConfirmation(userId, 'exec', params);\n 236→    await logAuditEntry({\n 237→      userId,\n 238→      role: getUserRole(userId),\n 239→      action: 'exec',\n 240→      params: { command },\n 241→      result: 'pending_confirmation',\n 242→      reason: `High-risk keywords: ${riskResult.detectedKeywords.join(', ')}`,\n 243→      sessionId\n 244→    });\n 245→    return {\n 246→      needsConfirmation: true,\n 247→      confirmationId: confirmId,\n 248→      confirmationMessage: message,\n 249→      detectedKeywords: riskResult.detectedKeywords\n 250→    };\n 251→  }\n 252→\n 253→  // If confirmation ID provided, verify it\n 254→  if (confirmationId) {\n 255→    const confirmResult = confirmAction(confirmationId, userId);\n 256→    if (!confirmResult.ok) {\n 257→      throw new Error(`确认失败：${confirmResult.error}`);\n 258→    }\n 259→  }\n 260→\n 261→  // Get session cwd\n 262→  const cwd = sessionStore.getCwd(sessionId) || process.cwd();\n 263→\n 264→  // Execute the command\n 265→  let result;\n 266→  try {\n 267→    result = await executeSystemCommand(command, { cwd });\n 268→  } catch (error) {\n 269→    await logAuditEntry({\n 270→      userId,\n 271→      role: getUserRole(userId),\n 272→      action: 'exec',\n 273→      params: { command, cwd },\n 274→      result: 'failed',\n 275→      reason: error.message,\n 276→      sessionId\n 277→    });\n 278→    throw error;\n 279→  }\n 280→\n 281→  // Format output\n 282→  const output = formatOutput(result);\n 283→  const pages = paginateOutput(output);\n 284→  const displayOutput = pages[0];\n 285→\n 286→  // Store remaining pages for /more\n 287→  if (pages.length > 1) {\n 288→    storeOutputPages(sessionId, pages.slice(1));\n 289→  }\n 290→\n 291→  // Log successful execution\n 292→  await logAuditEntry({\n 293→    userId,\n 294→    role: getUserRole(userId),\n 295→    action: 'exec',\n 296→    params: { command, cwd },\n 297→    result: 'success',\n 298→    sessionId\n 299→  });\n 300→\n 301→  // F-013: Record command in history\n 302→  sessionStore.recordCommand(sessionId, command, result.exitCode);\n 303→\n 304→  return {\n 305→    stdout: result.stdout,\n 306→    stderr: result.stderr,\n 307→    exitCode: result.exitCode,\n 308→    timedOut: result.timedOut,\n 309→    output: displayOutput,\n 310→    hasMorePages: hasMorePages(sessionId),\n 311→    needsConfirmation: false\n 312→  };\n 313→}\n 314→\n 315→function formatOutput(result) {\n 316→  const parts = [];\n 317→  if (result.timedOut) {\n 318→    parts.push(`⚠️ 命令执行超时，已终止进程。`);\n 319→  }\n 320→  parts.push(`exitCode: ${result.exitCode}`);\n 321→  if (result.stdout) {\n 322→    parts.push(`stdout:\\n${result.stdout}`);\n 323→  } else {\n 324→    parts.push(`stdout: (empty)`);\n 325→  }\n 326→  if (result.stderr) {\n 327→    parts.push(`stderr:\\n${result.stderr}`);\n 328→  } else {\n 329→    parts.push(`stderr: (empty)`);\n 330→  }\n 331→  return parts.join('\\n\\n');\n 332→}\n 333→\n 334→export default { executeCommand, confirmHighRiskCommand };\n 335→```\n 336→\n 337→### src/services/alert-manager-service.js (persistence pattern reference)\n 338→```javascript\n 339→/**\n 340→ * Alert Manager Service\n 341→ * F-012: System Monitor\n 342→ *\n 343→ * Manages alert rules, threshold monitoring, and notifications.\n 344→ * Reference for persistence pattern used in F-014.\n 345→ */\n 346→\n 347→import { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\n 348→import { mkdir, readFile, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\n 349→import { join } from 'node:path';\n 350→import { config } from '../config.js';\n 351→\n 352→export class AlertManagerService {\n 353→  constructor(options = {}) {\n 354→    this.dataDir = options.dataDir || config.systemMonitorDataDir;\n 355→    this.rulesFile = options.rulesFile || 'alert-rules.json';\n 356→    this.cooldownMs = options.cooldownMs || 5 * 60 * 1000;\n 357→    this.rules = new Map();\n 358→    this.lastTriggered = new Map();\n 359→    this.monitorInterval = null;\n 360→    this.pushCallback = null;\n 361→  }\n 362→\n 363→  addRule(ruleData) {\n 364→    this._validateRule(ruleData);\n 365→    const id = randomUUID();\n 366→    const rule = {\n 367→      id,\n 368→      metric: ruleData.metric,\n 369→      operator: ruleData.operator,\n 370→      threshold: ruleData.threshold,\n 371→      enabled: ruleData.enabled ?? true,\n 372→      createdAt: Date.now()\n 373→    };\n 374→    this.rules.set(id, rule);\n 375→    return { ...rule };\n 376→  }\n 377→\n 378→  removeRule(ruleId) {\n 379→    if (!this.rules.has(ruleId)) return false;\n 380→    this.rules.delete(ruleId);\n 381→    this.lastTriggered.delete(ruleId);\n 382→    return true;\n 383→  }\n 384→\n 385→  listRules() {\n 386→    return Array.from(this.rules.values()).map(rule => ({ ...rule }));\n 387→  }\n 388→\n 389→  async loadRules() {\n 390→    try {\n 391→      const filePath = join(this.dataDir, this.rulesFile);\n 392→      const content = await readFile(filePath, 'utf-8');\n 393→      const rules = JSON.parse(content);\n 394→      this.rules.clear();\n 395→      for (const rule of rules) {\n 396→        if (rule.id && rule.metric) {\n 397→          this.rules.set(rule.id, rule);\n 398→        }\n 399→      }\n 400→    } catch (error) {\n 401→      this.rules.clear();\n 402→    }\n 403→  }\n 404→\n 405→  async saveRules() {\n 406→    try {\n 407→      await mkdir(this.dataDir, { recursive: true });\n 408→      const filePath = join(this.dataDir, this.rulesFile);\n 409→      const rules = Array.from(this.rules.values());\n 410→      await writeFile(filePath, JSON.stringify(rules, null, 2), 'utf-8');\n 411→    } catch (error) {\n 412→      throw new Error(`Failed to save alert rules: ${error.message}`);\n 413→    }\n 414→  }\n 415→}\n 416→\n 417→export const alertManagerService = new AlertManagerService();\n 418→export default AlertManagerService;\n 419→```\n 420→\n 421→### src/services/session-context-service.js (singleton pattern reference)\n 422→```javascript\n 423→/**\n 424→ * Session Context Service\n 425→ * F-013: Session and Context Manager\n 426→ *\n 427→ * Manages session lifecycle, persistence, and timeout handling.\n 428→ * Reference for singleton and persistence patterns used in F-014.\n 429→ */\n 430→\n 431→import { mkdir, readFile, writeFile, unlink, readdir } from 'node:fs/promises';\n 432→import { join } from 'node:path';\n 433→import { config } from '../config.js';\n 434→import { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n 435→\n 436→class SessionContextServiceClass {\n 437→  #dataDir = null;\n 438→  #notificationCallback = null;\n 439→  #timeoutWatcherId = null;\n 440→  #isInitialized = false;\n 441→  #timeoutMs = null;\n 442→  #checkIntervalMs = null;\n 443→\n 444→  reset() {\n 445→    this.#dataDir = null;\n 446→    this.#notificationCallback = null;\n 447→    if (this.#timeoutWatcherId) {\n 448→      clearInterval(this.#timeoutWatcherId);\n 449→      this.#timeoutWatcherId = null;\n 450→    }\n 451→    this.#isInitialized = false;\n 452→  }\n 453→\n 454→  isInitialized() {\n 455→    return this.#isInitialized;\n 456→  }\n 457→\n 458→  initSessionContext({ dataDir, timeoutMs, checkIntervalMs }) {\n 459→    this.#dataDir = dataDir;\n 460→    this.#timeoutMs = timeoutMs || config.sessionTimeoutMs;\n 461→    this.#checkIntervalMs = checkIntervalMs || 60000;\n 462→    this.#isInitialized = true;\n 463→  }\n 464→\n 465→  #checkInitialized() {\n 466→    if (!this.#isInitialized) {\n 467→      throw new Error('SessionContextService not initialized. Call initSessionContext first.');\n 468→    }\n 469→  }\n 470→\n 471→  async #ensureDataDir() {\n 472→    if (this.#dataDir) {\n 473→      await mkdir(this.#dataDir, { recursive: true });\n 474→    }\n 475→  }\n 476→\n 477→  setNotificationCallback(callback) {\n 478→    this.#notificationCallback = callback;\n 479→  }\n 480→\n 481→  async persistSession(sessionKey) {\n 482→    this.#checkInitialized();\n 483→    await this.#ensureDataDir();\n 484→    const info = sessionStore.getSessionInfo(sessionKey);\n 485→    if (!info) {\n 486→      throw new Error(`Session ${sessionKey} not found`);\n 487→    }\n 488→    const data = {\n 489→      sessionKey: info.sessionKey,\n 490→      userId: info.userId,\n 491→      cwd: sessionStore.getCwd(sessionKey),\n 492→      envOverrides: sessionStore.getEnvOverrides(sessionKey),\n 493→      commandHistory: sessionStore.getCommandHistory(sessionKey),\n 494→      createdAt: info.createdAt,\n 495→      lastActivityAt: info.lastActivityAt\n 496→    };\n 497→    const filePath = this.#getSessionFilePath(sessionKey);\n 498→    await writeFile(filePath, JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n 499→  }\n 500→\n 501→  async restoreSessions() {\n 502→    this.#checkInitialized();\n 503→    try {\n 504→      const files = await readdir(this.#dataDir);\n 505→      const sessionFiles = files.filter((f) => f.endsWith('.json'));\n 506→      for (const file of sessionFiles) {\n 507→        try {\n 508→          const filePath = join(this.#dataDir, file);\n 509→          const content = await readFile(filePath, 'utf-8');\n 510→          const data = JSON.parse(content);\n 511→          const idleTime = Date.now() - (data.lastActivityAt || 0);\n 512→          if (idleTime > this.#timeoutMs) {\n 513→            await unlink(filePath);\n 514→            continue;\n 515→          }\n 516→          const { sessionKey, userId, cwd, envOverrides } = data;\n 517→          sessionStore.touchSession(sessionKey, userId);\n 518→          if (cwd) sessionStore.setCwd(sessionKey, cwd);\n 519→          for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(envOverrides || {})) {\n 520→            sessionStore.setEnvOverride(sessionKey, key, value);\n 521→          }\n 522→        } catch (error) {\n 523→          console.error(`Failed to restore session from ${file}:`, error.message);\n 524→        }\n 525→      }\n 526→    } catch (error) {\n 527→      if (error.code !== 'ENOENT') throw error;\n 528→    }\n 529→  }\n 530→}\n 531→\n 532→export const sessionContextService = new SessionContextServiceClass();\n 533→```\n 534→\n 535→### src/bot/commands/handlers/monitor.js (handler pattern reference)\n 536→```javascript\n 537→/**\n 538→ * /monitor Command Handler\n 539→ * F-012: System Monitor\n 540→ *\n 541→ * Reference for handler pattern with subcommands.\n 542→ */\n 543→\n 544→import { alertManagerService } from '../../../services/alert-manager-service.js';\n 545→import { escapeMarkdownV2 } from '../../../utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js';\n 546→\n 547→export const monitorMeta = {\n 548→  name: 'monitor',\n 549→  aliases: [],\n 550→  description: '管理系统监控告警规则',\n 551→  usage: '/monitor <set|list|remove|enable|disable> [参数]',\n 552→  examples: [\n 553→    '/monitor set cpu>80',\n 554→    '/monitor list',\n 555→    '/monitor remove <规则ID>'\n 556→  ],\n 557→  params: [],\n 558→  requiresAuth: true,\n 559→  minRole: 'operator',\n 560→  helpText: '/monitor <子命令> [参数]\\n' +\n 561→    '子命令:\\n' +\n 562→    '  set <规则>      添加告警规则\\n' +\n 563→    '  list           列出所有告警规则\\n' +\n 564→    '  remove <ID>    删除规则\\n' +\n 565→    '  enable <ID>    启用规则\\n' +\n 566→    '  disable <ID>   禁用规则'\n 567→};\n 568→\n 569→export function parseSubcommand(args) {\n 570→  if (!args || args.length === 0) {\n 571→    return { subcommand: '' };\n 572→  }\n 573→  const subcommand = args[0].toLowerCase();\n 574→  const arg = args.slice(1).join(' ');\n 575→  return { subcommand, arg };\n 576→}\n 577→\n 578→export async function handleMonitor(handlerCtx) {\n 579→  const { reply, args = [] } = handlerCtx;\n 580→  const { subcommand, arg } = parseSubcommand(args);\n 581→\n 582→  switch (subcommand) {\n 583→    case 'set':\n 584→      await handleSet(arg, reply);\n 585→      break;\n 586→    case 'list':\n 587→      await handleList(reply);\n 588→      break;\n 589→    case 'remove':\n 590→      await handleRemove(arg, reply);\n 591→      break;\n 592→    case 'enable':\n 593→      await handleToggle(arg, true, reply);\n 594→      break;\n 595→    case 'disable':\n 596→      await handleToggle(arg, false, reply);\n 597→      break;\n 598→    default:\n 599→      await reply('📋 *监控告警命令用法*\\n...');\n 600→  }\n 601→}\n 602→```\n 603→\n 604→### src/bot/telegram.js (bot initialization pattern)\n 605→```javascript\n 606→import { Telegraf } from 'telegraf';\n 607→import { config } from '../config.js';\n 608→import { sessionContextService } from '../services/session-context-service.js';\n 609→import { aliasStore } from '../services/alias-store.js';\n 610→import { registerCommand, routeCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n 611→\n 612→export async function createTelegramBot() {\n 613→  const bot = new Telegraf(config.telegramBotToken, {\n 614→    handlerTimeout: 10 * 60 * 1000\n 615→  });\n 616→\n 617→  // F-013: Initialize services\n 618→  await sessionContextService.initSessionContext({ dataDir: config.sessionPersistenceDir });\n 619→  await aliasStore.initAliasStore({ filePath: config.aliasPersistencePath });\n 620→\n 621→  // F-013: Restore from disk\n 622→  await sessionContextService.restoreSessions();\n 623→\n 624→  // F-013: Set up notification callback\n 625→  sessionContextService.setNotificationCallback(async (sessionKey, userId) => {\n 626→    try {\n 627→      const chatId = sessionKey.replace('telegram:', '');\n 628→      await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, '⏰ 会话因长时间未活动已超时。');\n 629→    } catch (error) {\n 630→      console.error('Failed to send timeout notification:', error);\n 631→    }\n 632→  });\n 633→\n 634→  // F-013: Start timeout watcher\n 635→  sessionContextService.startTimeoutWatcher();\n 636→\n 637→  // Register commands\n 638→  registerCommand(monitorMeta, handleMonitor);\n 639→  // ... other commands\n 640→\n 641→  bot.on('text', async (ctx) => {\n 642→    const handled = await routeCommand(ctx);\n 643→    if (handled) return;\n 644→    // ... fallback handling\n 645→  });\n 646→\n 647→  return bot;\n 648→}\n 649→```\n 650→\n 651→---\n 652→\n 653→## Section 5 — Existing Tests\n 654→\n 655→### Test patterns used in the project:\n 656→\n 657→```javascript\n 658→// tests/helpers/helpers.test.js pattern\n 659→import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\n 660→\n 661→// Singleton reset pattern for testing\n 662→service.reset();\n 663→\n 664→// Mock telegram context\n 665→const mockCtx = {\n 666→  reply: vi.fn(),\n 667→  from: { id: '123456789' },\n 668→  chat: { id: '123456789' }\n 669→};\n 670→\n 671→// Test with temporary directory\n 672→const tempDir = await fs.mkdtemp(path.join(os.tmpdir(), 'test-'));\n 673→```\n 674→\n 675→### tests/services/alert-manager-service.test.js (persistence test pattern)\n 676→```javascript\n 677→import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\n 678→import { AlertManagerService } from '../../src/services/alert-manager-service.js';\n 679→import { mkdir, rm, readFile, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\n 680→import { join } from 'node:path';\n 681→import os from 'node:os';\n 682→\n 683→describe('AlertManagerService', () => {\n 684→  let service;\n 685→  let tempDir;\n 686→\n 687→  beforeEach(async () => {\n 688→    tempDir = await mkdtemp(join(os.tmpdir(), 'alert-test-'));\n 689→    service = new AlertManagerService({ dataDir: tempDir });\n 690→  });\n 691→\n 692→  afterEach(async () => {\n 693→    await rm(tempDir, { recursive: true, force: true });\n 694→  });\n 695→\n 696→  it('should persist rules to disk', async () => {\n 697→    service.addRule({ metric: 'cpu', operator: '>', threshold: 80, enabled: true });\n 698→    await service.saveRules();\n 699→\n 700→    const content = await readFile(join(tempDir, 'alert-rules.json'), 'utf-8');\n 701→    const rules = JSON.parse(content);\n 702→    expect(rules).toHaveLength(1);\n 703→    expect(rules[0].metric).toBe('cpu');\n 704→  });\n 705→\n 706→  it('should restore rules from disk', async () => {\n 707→    await writeFile(join(tempDir, 'alert-rules.json'), JSON.stringify([\n 708→      { id: 'test-id', metric: 'memory', operator: '>=', threshold: 90, enabled: true }\n 709→    ]));\n 710→\n 711→    await service.loadRules();\n 712→    const rules = service.listRules();\n 713→    expect(rules).toHaveLength(1);\n 714→  });\n 715→});\n 716→```\n 717→\n 718→---\n 719→\n 720→## Section 6 — Key Design Decisions\n 721→\n 722→### Architecture Decisions for F-014:\n 723→\n 724→1. **Scheduled Tasks Service** (new file: `src/services/scheduled-task-service.js`)\n 725→   - Use singleton pattern like `sessionContextService`\n 726→   - Support cron expressions via `node-cron` or `croner` library\n 727→   - Support one-time tasks with scheduled execution\n 728→   - Store tasks in `data/scheduled-tasks.json`\n 729→   - On task execution, use `executeCommand` from F-009\n 730→   - Push results to Telegram via bot instance\n 731→\n 732→2. **File Watcher Service** (new file: `src/services/file-watcher-service.js`)\n 733→   - Use `fs.watch` for file/directory monitoring\n 734→   - Store watchers in `data/file-watchers.json`\n 735→   - Support multiple watch targets per user\n 736→   - Debounce rapid change events (500ms default)\n 737→   - Push notifications to Telegram on change\n 738→\n 739→3. **Command Handlers**\n 740→   - `/cron` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/cron.js`\n 741→   - `/jobs` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.js`\n 742→   - `/watch` handler in `src/bot/commands/handlers/watch.js`\n 743→\n 744→4. **Configuration**\n 745→   - `SCHEDULED_TASKS_PATH`: Path for task persistence\n 746→   - `FILE_WATCHERS_PATH`: Path for watcher persistence\n 747→   - `MAX_SCHEDULED_TASKS`: Maximum tasks allowed (default 100)\n 748→   - `MAX_FILE_WATCHERS`: Maximum watchers allowed (default 50)\n 749→   - `TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS`: Debounce for file changes (default 500)\n 750→\n 751→5. **Integration Points**\n 752→   - Initialize services in `createTelegramBot()`\n 753→   - Restore tasks/watchers on startup\n 754→   - Store bot instance reference for notifications\n 755→\n 756→---\n 757→\n 758→## Implementation Log\n 759→\n 760→### Files Created\n 761→\n 762→1. **src/services/scheduled-task-service.js**\n 763→   - Singleton service for managing scheduled tasks\n 764→   - Supports cron expressions and one-time tasks via `croner` library\n 765→   - Implements addCronTask, addOneTimeTask, listTasks, pauseTask, resumeTask, deleteTask, executeTask\n 766→   - Includes persistence (saveTasks/loadTasks), scheduler lifecycle (startScheduler/stopScheduler)\n 767→   - Integrates with executeCommand for task execution and Telegram for notifications\n 768→\n 769→2. **src/services/file-watcher-service.js**\n 770→   - Singleton service for file system monitoring\n 771→   - Uses native `fs.watch` with configurable debouncing (default 500ms)\n 772→   - Implements addWatch, removeWatch, listWatches, startWatching, stopWatching, stopAllWatchers\n 773→   - Includes persistence (saveWatches/loadWatches), restoreWatches for restart recovery\n 774→   - Path validation against allowed roots (TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS)\n 775→\n 776→3. **src/bot/commands/handlers/cron.js**\n 777→   - Handler for /cron add command\n 778→   - Parses cron expressions and datetime strings for one-time tasks\n 779→   - Validates cron expressions using croner library\n 780→   - Delegates to scheduledTaskService\n 781→\n 782→4. **src/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.js**\n 783→   - Handler for /jobs command with subcommands: list, pause, resume, delete\n 784→   - Supports partial ID matching for task operations\n 785→   - Filters tasks by chatId\n 786→\n 787→5. **src/bot/commands/handlers/watch.js**\n 788→   - Handler for /watch and /unwatch commands\n 789→   - Supports /watch list, /watch <path>, /unwatch <path|ID>\n 790→   - Path validation and normalization\n 791→\n 792→### Files Modified\n 793→\n 794→1. **src/config.js**\n 795→   - Added F-014 config options:\n 796→     - SCHEDULED_TASKS_PATH (default: 'data/scheduled-tasks.json')\n 797→     - FILE_WATCHERS_PATH (default: 'data/file-watchers.json')\n 798→     - MAX_SCHEDULED_TASKS (default: 100)\n 799→     - MAX_FILE_WATCHERS (default: 50)\n 800→     - TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS (default: 500)\n 801→\n 802→2. **src/services/index.js**\n 803→   - Exported scheduledTaskService and fileWatcherService\n 804→\n 805→3. **src/bot/telegram.js**\n 806→   - Imported F-014 services and command handlers\n 807→   - Initialized scheduledTaskService with executeCallback and notificationCallback\n 808→   - Initialized fileWatcherService with notificationCallback\n 809→   - Added service restoration on startup (loadTasks, loadWatches, restoreWatches)\n 810→   - Registered /cron, /jobs, /watch commands\n 811→   - Added helper function truncate() for output formatting\n 812→\n 813→4. **package.json**\n 814→   - Added dependency: croner (^9.0.0)\n 815→\n 816→### Key Implementation Decisions\n 817→\n 818→1. **Cron Library Selection**\n 819→   - Chose `croner` over `node-cron` for its lightweight footprint and clean API\n 820→   - Supports standard 5-field cron expressions\n 821→   - Provides nextRun calculation for task scheduling\n 822→\n 823→2. **Singleton Pattern**\n 824→   - Both services use singleton pattern similar to sessionContextService\n 825→   - Reset method for testing isolation\n 826→   - Init methods for configuration injection\n 827→\n 828→3. **Task Execution Flow**\n 829→   - Tasks use executeCommand with skipConfirmation=true (scheduled tasks are pre-approved)\n 830→   - Results captured in lastResult field with stdout/stderr/exitCode/timedOut\n 831→   - Telegram notifications sent via callback pattern for decoupling\n 832→\n 833→4. **File Watcher Debouncing**\n 834→   - 500ms default debounce to prevent rapid-fire notifications\n 835→   - Configurable via TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n 836→   - Per-watcher debounce timers for independent operation\n 837→\n 838→5. **Persistence Strategy**\n 839→   - Tasks/watchers stored as JSON arrays in data/ directory\n 840→   - Loaded on startup with graceful handling of missing/corrupted files\n 841→   - One-time tasks automatically deleted after execution\n 842→\n 843→### Deviations from plan.md\n 844→\n 845→1. **No separate bot.prizm update needed**\n 846→   - runtime.prizm and services.prizm already contained sufficient documentation\n 847→   - Command documentation added to INTERFACES section of runtime.prizm\n 848→\n 849→2. **Added setExecuteCallback method**\n 850→   - Not in original plan but necessary for clean integration with executeCommand\n 851→   - Allows service to delegate command execution to the configured callback\n 852→\n 853→3. **Added truncate helper to telegram.js**\n 854→   - Utility function for truncating long output in notifications\n 855→   - Keeps Telegram messages within reasonable limits\n 856→\n 857→### Test Coverage\n 858→\n 859→- 87 tests total across unit and integration tests\n 860→- Config validation: 6 tests\n 861→- ScheduledTaskService: 25 tests\n 862→- FileWatcherService: 21 tests\n 863→- Command handlers (cron, jobs, watch): 21 tests\n 864→- Integration tests: 14 tests\n 865→\n 866→All tests pass successfully.\n 867→\n 868→---\n 869→\n 870→## Implementation Log\n 871→\n 872→### Files Created\n 873→\n 874→1. **src/services/scheduled-task-service.js** - Singleton service for managing scheduled tasks with cron expressions and one-time execution\n 875→2. **src/services/file-watcher-service.js** - Singleton service for file system monitoring with fs.watch and debouncing\n 876→3. **src/bot/commands/handlers/cron.js** - Command handler for /cron command (add scheduled tasks)\n 877→4. **src/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.js** - Command handler for /jobs command (list/pause/resume/delete tasks)\n 878→5. **src/bot/commands/handlers/watch.js** - Command handler for /watch and /unwatch commands\n 879→6. **tests/services/scheduled-task-service.test.js** - Unit tests for scheduled task service\n 880→7. **tests/services/file-watcher-service.test.js** - Unit tests for file watcher service\n 881→8. **tests/bot/commands/handlers/cron.test.js** - Unit tests for cron command handler\n 882→9. **tests/bot/commands/handlers/jobs.test.js** - Unit tests for jobs command handler\n 883→10. **tests/bot/commands/handlers/watch.test.js** - Unit tests for watch command handler\n 884→11. **tests/config/f014-config.test.js** - Configuration tests\n 885→12. **tests/integration/f014-scheduled-tasks.test.js** - Integration tests for scheduled tasks\n 886→13. **tests/integration/f014-file-watchers.test.js** - Integration tests for file watchers\n 887→\n 888→### Files Modified\n 889→\n 890→1. **src/config.js** - Added F-014 configuration options: SCHEDULED_TASKS_PATH, FILE_WATCHERS_PATH, MAX_SCHEDULED_TASKS, MAX_FILE_WATCHERS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n 891→2. **src/services/index.js** - Added exports for scheduledTaskService and fileWatcherService\n 892→3. **src/bot/telegram.js** - Already had F-014 integration (service initialization, notification callbacks, command registration)\n 893→4. **package.json** - Added croner dependency for cron expression parsing\n 894→5. **.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm** - Updated with F-014 interfaces and traps\n 895→6. **.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm** - Updated with new service APIs and traps\n 896→7. **.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm** - Already documented with F-014 commands\n 897→\n 898→### Key Implementation Decisions\n 899→\n 900→1. **Cron Library Selection**: Chose `croner` over `node-cron` for lighter weight and simpler API\n 901→2. **Singleton Pattern**: Both services use singleton pattern with `reset()` method for testability\n 902→3. **Persistence Format**: Tasks and watchers stored as JSON arrays in data/ directory\n 903→4. **Task Execution**: Uses existing `executeCommand` from F-009 with `skipConfirmation: true`\n 904→5. **Notification Callbacks**: Both services use callback pattern for Telegram notifications, set during bot initialization\n 905→6. **One-time Task Cleanup**: Automatically delete one-time tasks after successful execution\n 906→7. **File Watcher Debouncing**: 500ms default debounce to prevent notification spam\n 907→\n 908→### Deviations from plan.md\n 909→\n 910→1. No deviations - implementation followed the plan.md design exactly\n 911→2. Telegram.js already had F-014 integration code pre-written\n 912→\n 913→### Test Results\n 914→\n 915→All 87 F-014 tests pass:\n 916→- 6 config tests\n 917→- 25 scheduled-task-service tests  \n 918→- 21 file-watcher-service tests\n 919→- 10 cron handler tests\n 920→- 10 jobs handler tests\n 921→- 4 watch handler tests\n 922→- 5 scheduled-tasks integration tests\n 923→- 7 file-watchers integration tests\n 924→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_856b2e0610214177b9bb07b6","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:52:05.246Z","_requestId":"0897e02cbc65495fa1b66af82a5de7ab"}
